WEBVTT

01:39.470 --> 01:43.190
[Road to Success]

01:44.759 --> 01:47.880
[Episode 19]

01:48.060 --> 01:49.870
You have to admit I played really well.

01:49.870 --> 01:50.590
Coach gave me that...

01:50.590 --> 01:51.120
Come on.

01:51.120 --> 01:52.120
Coach.

01:52.640 --> 01:53.479
Coach.

01:53.479 --> 01:54.610
That pass of mine...

01:55.150 --> 01:56.810
That was exceptionally good.

01:56.920 --> 01:59.070
That was amazing.

02:00.790 --> 02:02.430
Coach, did you see us play?

02:02.430 --> 02:04.280
-We played so well. Aren't you going to praise us?
-Yeah.

02:04.280 --> 02:05.590
Great job today.

02:05.590 --> 02:07.150
Did you thank Ms. Lin?

02:10.240 --> 02:12.520
Thank you, Ms. Lin.

02:13.680 --> 02:14.910
I'm the team supervisor.

02:14.910 --> 02:15.910
It's my duty.

02:18.120 --> 02:19.680
How was my pass?

02:19.680 --> 02:21.190
-I told you.
-That was a great strategy.

02:21.190 --> 02:22.840
You can never go wrong
believing in yourself.

02:22.840 --> 02:23.870
We were bound to win.

02:23.870 --> 02:24.800
What a cool win.

02:24.800 --> 02:25.870
Cool as hell.

02:25.870 --> 02:27.800
Yes, you're the coolest.

02:31.870 --> 02:34.079
Isn't this that trendy spot
with the super long lines?

02:34.079 --> 02:36.960
Yes, this is a reward from your coach.

02:36.960 --> 02:38.840
Come on! Eat up!

02:38.840 --> 02:39.680
-Thank you, Coach!
-Coach!

02:39.680 --> 02:41.520
-Good for you!
-Coach!

02:42.000 --> 02:43.360
I'm starving!

02:45.120 --> 02:46.120
What do you want to eat?

02:46.120 --> 02:47.030
I'll go get it.

02:47.520 --> 02:49.840
I've had a toothache lately,
and I have things to do.

02:49.840 --> 02:51.000
You guys go ahead and eat.

02:51.000 --> 02:51.890
-Fu.
-Can we take whatever we like?

02:51.890 --> 02:53.450
Babies, I'm leaving now.

02:54.560 --> 02:55.840
We can finish it, bro.

03:01.800 --> 03:03.240
This doesn't feel right.

03:13.960 --> 03:15.310
Surprise.

03:16.520 --> 03:17.710
Li?

03:19.590 --> 03:22.590
Congratulations
on your triumphant return, Ms. Lin.

03:24.960 --> 03:25.620
Let's go in.

03:30.120 --> 03:30.920
What's wrong?

03:31.310 --> 03:32.510
Are you feeling down?

03:32.750 --> 03:34.280
Didn't the team win today?

03:35.710 --> 03:36.910
I'm not unhappy.

03:37.240 --> 03:39.090
The kids did great.

03:39.360 --> 03:40.470
I'm just...

03:43.900 --> 03:44.900
a little tired.

03:48.310 --> 03:49.770
You don't have to lie to me.

03:54.030 --> 03:55.829
What did you buy? Fried chicken?

03:58.750 --> 04:00.400
Do you want me to stay with you,

04:00.400 --> 04:02.400
or do you want to be alone for a while?

04:04.360 --> 04:05.030
I...

04:06.840 --> 04:07.430
Okay.

04:09.000 --> 04:11.120
If it gets cold, microwave it.

04:11.120 --> 04:12.150
Don't eat it cold.

04:13.400 --> 04:14.150
Take care.

04:53.820 --> 04:54.909
[Little Savage Tribe]

05:25.310 --> 05:26.190
Li?

05:31.070 --> 05:32.200
I knew you were home.

05:33.270 --> 05:35.870
I bought some barbecue
for a late-night snack.

05:36.070 --> 05:36.930
I'm not hungry.

05:37.890 --> 05:39.290
You blocked me on WeChat.

05:40.630 --> 05:42.190
Can I ask why?

05:50.190 --> 05:51.000
Ming...

05:54.720 --> 05:55.680
is Jason.

05:59.840 --> 06:00.720
right?

06:07.610 --> 06:10.010
I know you don't want to talk to me
right now,

06:10.560 --> 06:12.220
but I already have some clues.

06:12.750 --> 06:14.240
I have a notebook.

06:14.240 --> 06:16.440
It contains my investigation results.

06:16.630 --> 06:18.290
You can take a look at it first.

06:32.490 --> 06:33.300
[A Rising Star Falls: Reports Say]

06:33.320 --> 06:34.070
[Nanton's Most Promising
Chinese Football Player Dies by Suicide]

06:39.540 --> 06:42.600
[Somatization of Depression]

06:46.240 --> 06:46.860
[The Michelangelo Phenomenon:]

06:46.880 --> 06:47.520
[The Psychological Struggles
of Perfectionists]

06:47.670 --> 06:49.610
[Somatization of Depression]

06:52.650 --> 06:54.570
[Brintellix]

06:55.500 --> 06:56.880
[The IP of Spade Q]
[It was London Psychology]

06:56.900 --> 06:58.880
[Research Institute] [This place is
a historic academic institution in London.]

06:59.370 --> 07:00.910
[Source of the prohibited drugs]
[Jason's Activities and Daily Diet]

07:00.940 --> 07:02.880
[Before the Incident]
[There was only a bottle of gummy bears]

07:03.730 --> 07:04.550
[I didn't go out. I hate rainy days.]

07:04.580 --> 07:05.490
[It's raining today.]
[Did you catch a new firefly?]

07:05.840 --> 07:06.580
[I found fireflies downstairs today.]

07:06.600 --> 07:07.280
[It's the rarest type.
I'll send a picture to you.]

07:07.300 --> 07:08.060
[I can tell that rainy days
are your favorite, but...]

07:08.080 --> 07:09.050
[How will you get there?
You should learn how to ride a bike.]

07:09.160 --> 07:10.160
[Hate rainy days.]

07:10.710 --> 07:11.670
[Hahaha. Tell me about it]

07:16.710 --> 07:17.490
[By the way, about the gift,]

07:17.510 --> 07:18.470
[can you not tell anyone?]

07:18.500 --> 07:19.510
[Don't forget to eat it.]

07:19.530 --> 07:20.700
[I'll get mad if they go to waste.]

07:20.720 --> 07:21.870
[Jokes aside, I'll send you a gift later.]

07:21.900 --> 07:22.960
[Remember to accept it.]

07:27.600 --> 07:28.560
[Jokes aside, I'll send you a gift later.]

07:28.580 --> 07:29.500
[Remember to accept it.]

07:29.530 --> 07:30.490
[Thank you. In the UK,]

07:30.510 --> 07:31.480
[you're the first friend
to send me a gift.]

07:38.330 --> 07:40.460
[Two Lin Wanxings]

07:41.630 --> 07:42.750
Two?

07:43.520 --> 07:44.510
[Two Lin Wanxings]

07:44.540 --> 07:47.150
[The reason for his death]
[The gift from Spade Q]

07:47.180 --> 07:48.790
[She told Jason not to tell anyone.]

07:48.820 --> 07:49.950
[Different people]

08:07.750 --> 08:08.630
Let's talk.

08:16.270 --> 08:17.930
You've read the files?

08:22.070 --> 08:23.750
I met Ming

08:25.190 --> 08:26.950
on a psychology forum.

08:28.630 --> 08:30.000
He posted a thread,

08:31.750 --> 08:34.010
saying he suffered from severe insomnia

08:34.510 --> 08:35.789
and sometimes

08:35.789 --> 08:37.390
even wanted to hurt himself.

08:40.200 --> 08:43.150
So I added him on QQ to chat with him.

08:45.110 --> 08:46.550
His parents

08:46.870 --> 08:49.600
divorced because of arguments
when he was young.

08:50.150 --> 08:51.410
His father was absent.

08:53.290 --> 08:55.090
Because of his family of origin,

08:55.960 --> 08:56.960
he always had

08:56.960 --> 08:58.750
severe psychological trauma.

09:00.630 --> 09:01.840
He always thought

09:02.960 --> 09:04.960
it was because he wasn't good enough

09:06.510 --> 09:08.000
that he wasn't loved.

09:11.080 --> 09:12.390
If I had noticed

09:14.270 --> 09:16.400
his psychological problems earlier,

09:18.440 --> 09:20.640
maybe none of this would have happened.

09:24.870 --> 09:26.630
So you just said

09:28.000 --> 09:29.390
you found some clues.

09:32.000 --> 09:34.400
Is it really what you said
in your notebook?

09:35.240 --> 09:37.270
Someone impersonated me on my account

09:37.270 --> 09:39.870
and induced him to commit suicide
step by step?

09:53.720 --> 09:54.600
That person

09:56.150 --> 09:57.790
did something even worse.

10:01.600 --> 10:03.460
Do you remember that on Christmas

10:03.910 --> 10:05.970
you gave Ming a bottle of gummy bears?

10:09.510 --> 10:10.270
That person

10:11.840 --> 10:13.440
swapped that bottle of candy

10:15.240 --> 10:16.870
and added ephedrine to it.

10:21.030 --> 10:22.690
And as for what happened next,

10:24.870 --> 10:26.000
you already know.

10:29.840 --> 10:30.750
No wonder.

10:34.000 --> 10:36.840
No wonder his last message to me said

10:38.260 --> 10:39.380
he hated me.

10:47.130 --> 10:48.420
His death

10:50.540 --> 10:52.300
was indirectly caused by me.

10:53.430 --> 10:55.000
No, Lin Wanxing.

10:55.700 --> 10:57.560
That person is the real murderer.

11:05.180 --> 11:06.910
Does this look familiar to you?

11:10.070 --> 11:11.750
The person using this profile photo

11:11.750 --> 11:13.950
is the murderer who stole your account.

11:16.750 --> 11:17.670
A butterfly?

11:22.270 --> 11:23.510
Xiang Zi?

11:26.080 --> 11:27.420
Who is Xiang Zi?

11:30.360 --> 11:31.600
He is my senior.

11:32.240 --> 11:33.570
He's one grade above me.

11:34.090 --> 11:35.360
Because he took a year off,

11:35.360 --> 11:36.650
he was in the same grade as me.

11:36.650 --> 11:39.390
I remember he loved
studying butterfly specimens.

11:39.390 --> 11:40.150
Back then,

11:40.150 --> 11:42.390
it was him who went to the UK with me
for the exchange program.

11:42.390 --> 11:44.750
That was also when I met Ming.

11:46.840 --> 11:48.440
Then he is the prime suspect.

11:49.600 --> 11:51.600
Did you have any conflicts with him?

11:53.150 --> 11:54.680
I rejected his confession.

11:55.150 --> 11:57.150
That shouldn't count as a conflict.

12:03.750 --> 12:04.600
Wang Fa.

12:05.870 --> 12:08.010
I can't absolve myself from this.

12:08.870 --> 12:10.600
I want to investigate with you.

12:12.840 --> 12:13.630
Okay.

12:20.780 --> 12:21.580
Lin Wanxing,

12:24.510 --> 12:25.510
I want to say...

12:29.240 --> 12:30.360
I'm really sorry.

12:36.960 --> 12:38.850
At Xiang Zi's home in Lyujing,

12:38.950 --> 12:41.030
he takes on
some psychological counseling cases?

12:41.030 --> 12:42.480
He studied psychology,

12:42.480 --> 12:43.680
so he's very guarded.

12:43.870 --> 12:45.470
You won't be able
to get anything out of him.

12:45.470 --> 12:46.150
It's fine.

12:46.890 --> 12:48.820
We're going there for counseling.

13:46.530 --> 13:47.590
[Psychology Counseling Room]

13:52.670 --> 13:54.440
Here, have some tea.

14:03.360 --> 14:05.760
Half a spoonful of honey for you,
as always?

14:14.820 --> 14:16.400
You have a great memory.

14:16.630 --> 14:18.620
It's been over a year since we last met.

14:18.620 --> 14:19.620
How have you been?

14:20.840 --> 14:21.600
Pretty good.

14:24.360 --> 14:25.760
I'm glad you've moved on.

14:26.200 --> 14:27.860
I was quite worried about you.

14:28.690 --> 14:30.020
I wanted to contact you,

14:30.360 --> 14:32.360
but I didn't have your contact info.

14:38.630 --> 14:41.570
You opened a counseling clinic
only a year after graduation.

14:41.570 --> 14:42.810
Impressive.

14:43.760 --> 14:44.970
I'm not like you.

14:44.990 --> 14:46.650
I'm not cut out for academics.

14:46.690 --> 14:49.260
Graduating early and making money
suit me better.

14:49.260 --> 14:50.680
You're too modest.

14:51.200 --> 14:52.470
I forgot to introduce you to each other.

14:52.470 --> 14:54.160
This is my friend, Wang Fa.

14:56.690 --> 14:58.220
The main reason we came here

14:58.240 --> 15:00.240
is to ask for a favor.

15:00.960 --> 15:01.900
Go ahead.

15:01.970 --> 15:02.970
Let me.

15:04.170 --> 15:06.100
I need psychological counseling.

15:08.030 --> 15:10.030
What kind of counseling do you need?

15:10.600 --> 15:11.790
I had a student

15:12.870 --> 15:13.800
who passed away.

15:26.450 --> 15:28.250
For psychological counseling,

15:28.250 --> 15:29.510
my junior here can help you.

15:29.510 --> 15:30.870
Why did you come to me?

15:33.910 --> 15:35.240
Isn't it a rule

15:36.240 --> 15:37.970
not to counsel acquaintances?

15:41.480 --> 15:42.630
You two are close?

15:43.390 --> 15:44.630
How close are you?

15:46.150 --> 15:47.510
We work together.

15:47.510 --> 15:48.570
We're colleagues,

15:49.440 --> 15:50.810
and he's kind of

15:51.440 --> 15:52.600
my tenant.

15:52.620 --> 15:53.710
You live together?

15:54.960 --> 15:56.020
He lives upstairs.

16:03.120 --> 16:03.840
I see.

16:05.390 --> 16:06.670
As for the counseling,

16:06.900 --> 16:08.230
I need to think about it.

16:08.870 --> 16:10.780
I have something to do in half an hour.

16:10.780 --> 16:12.310
I won't keep you here today.

16:12.960 --> 16:14.080
I see.

16:14.390 --> 16:15.520
Sorry to bother you.

16:23.720 --> 16:25.320
Seeing these butterfly specimens

16:25.320 --> 16:26.440
reminds me of the time

16:26.440 --> 16:28.030
we were in grad school.

16:28.320 --> 16:29.550
I really miss those days.

16:29.550 --> 16:30.790
Back then,

16:30.790 --> 16:32.430
you weren't interested in these things.

16:32.430 --> 16:33.890
Things are different now.

16:34.870 --> 16:38.130
I'm looking forward
to taking a good look at them next time.

16:39.670 --> 16:41.330
We'll see if there's a chance.

16:42.080 --> 16:42.910
Let's go.

17:01.840 --> 17:02.970
Open the door for me.

17:19.130 --> 17:20.380
He's still watching.

17:20.400 --> 17:21.740
Put on a full show.

17:31.830 --> 17:32.960
Didn't you say that?

17:33.270 --> 17:34.380
Put on a full show.

17:40.090 --> 17:41.550
Do you think he will agree?

17:43.220 --> 17:44.310
Not necessarily.

17:45.270 --> 17:48.080
When we asked if we could come again,

17:48.100 --> 17:49.230
he hesitated.

17:49.830 --> 17:50.960
Then what do you think we should do

17:50.960 --> 17:52.490
to make him change his mind?

17:57.830 --> 17:59.590
What we are doing now is fine.

18:07.550 --> 18:08.440
It's working.

18:18.850 --> 18:20.960
[A Daily Dose of Psychology:
The Sweet Lemon Effect]

18:20.960 --> 18:22.160
[A Daily Dose of Psychology:
The Wallenda Effect]

18:27.180 --> 18:29.490
[See you at the studio at 10:00 a.m.
the day after tomorrow.]

18:28.880 --> 18:29.750
He agreed.

18:29.950 --> 18:32.430
We have an appointment at 10:00 a.m.
the day after tomorrow.

18:32.430 --> 18:33.590
Then we have a day and a half

18:33.590 --> 18:34.300
to prepare.

18:34.790 --> 18:36.070
What's your plan?

18:36.290 --> 18:38.270
I plan to create a personal website.

18:38.270 --> 18:39.680
I'll have Yu Bo imitate his tone

18:39.680 --> 18:41.030
and leave lots of comments on the website

18:41.030 --> 18:41.880
to attract him.

18:41.880 --> 18:43.640
Having Yu Bo empathize with him?

18:43.640 --> 18:45.680
If Xiang Zi relates to the comments,

18:46.070 --> 18:48.030
he might contact Yu Bo

18:48.370 --> 18:50.410
and share his past cases.

18:50.440 --> 18:52.700
The content and comments on the website

18:52.720 --> 18:54.350
have to be very precise.

18:55.330 --> 18:56.530
It's very difficult,

18:56.920 --> 18:57.880
but worth a try.

19:09.870 --> 19:12.140
Okay, it's done. Take a look.

19:14.600 --> 19:16.730
[Winfred Wang]

19:16.800 --> 19:17.490
[At 4 a.m., I am always the first one
to arrive at the locker room.]

19:17.520 --> 19:18.290
[The moment the lights come on,
the empty lockers]

19:18.310 --> 19:19.340
[look like unanswered questions
on a blank sheet of paper.]

19:18.760 --> 19:20.040
Why does it seem to me

19:20.070 --> 19:22.330
that these words aren't very effective?

19:23.720 --> 19:25.480
No, these are all moments of glory.

19:25.480 --> 19:27.070
How can they be ineffective?

19:27.070 --> 19:29.640
Yu Bo, different trades are worlds apart.

19:30.030 --> 19:32.200
The average person's attention
span on a webpage

19:32.200 --> 19:34.160
is about 6 to 8 seconds.

19:34.160 --> 19:35.270
If they have a purpose

19:35.270 --> 19:37.130
and want to search for something,

19:37.440 --> 19:38.440
maybe 15 seconds.

19:39.200 --> 19:40.160
In other words,

19:40.920 --> 19:42.270
within 15 seconds,

19:42.270 --> 19:43.160
if Xiang Zi

19:43.160 --> 19:44.830
doesn't see the information he wants,

19:44.830 --> 19:46.290
he will close the website.

19:47.400 --> 19:48.510
Then what should I do?

19:48.510 --> 19:50.440
What should I put up?

19:51.350 --> 19:53.240
I think we should put up some

19:53.240 --> 19:55.160
things he's interested in.

19:55.160 --> 19:56.960
Like butterflies.

19:58.590 --> 19:59.880
He likes butterflies.

20:00.510 --> 20:02.240
If I post these on the website,

20:02.960 --> 20:04.490
would it be too deliberate?

20:05.030 --> 20:05.750
That's why

20:05.750 --> 20:07.510
we need to show it casually.

20:07.510 --> 20:09.270
For example, we can find some photos

20:09.270 --> 20:10.590
and add a small butterfly element

20:10.590 --> 20:12.030
in the corners

20:12.030 --> 20:13.830
for him to discover by accident.

20:15.790 --> 20:17.720
Then what about the other content?

20:18.240 --> 20:20.640
It's best to reveal your inner thoughts.

20:21.550 --> 20:23.720
But once he searches my website,

20:23.720 --> 20:25.480
he'll know I'm Jason's coach.

20:25.480 --> 20:26.880
According to Kevin's info,

20:26.880 --> 20:28.400
he should know

20:28.400 --> 20:29.750
who he killed.

20:30.830 --> 20:31.590
Right.

20:31.790 --> 20:33.480
Usually, killers return to the crime scene

20:33.480 --> 20:34.680
for two reasons.

20:34.680 --> 20:36.680
The first is to destroy evidence

20:36.680 --> 20:38.070
and cover up the crime.

20:38.070 --> 20:38.750
The second

20:38.750 --> 20:40.550
is to satisfy their twisted desire
for control

20:40.550 --> 20:41.440
and sense of achievement.

20:41.440 --> 20:43.070
By reliving their actions,

20:43.070 --> 20:45.730
they can prove
their capability and influence.

20:45.960 --> 20:48.090
You are a victim of the Jason incident.

20:48.680 --> 20:50.480
You can satisfy this need of his.

20:50.880 --> 20:53.110
He will keep reading what you write.

21:02.750 --> 21:04.880
Okay, just write about your daily life.

21:04.880 --> 21:06.080
I'll look for photos.

21:12.170 --> 21:12.740
[Someone asked me why I became a coach.]

21:12.760 --> 21:13.450
[I think back to the first time I touched the ball,
and the tremble that ran through my fingertips.]

21:19.640 --> 21:20.160
[That was the moment
when my passion took root and grew.]

21:20.190 --> 21:20.770
[I want to help more people
find themselves on the football field.]

21:26.640 --> 21:28.240
What do you think of this one?

21:29.320 --> 21:30.450
It's not bad, right?

21:31.840 --> 21:32.840
It's pretty good.

21:34.260 --> 21:35.260
What do you think?

21:35.290 --> 21:36.420
The first one.

21:36.440 --> 21:37.480
The second one.

21:37.800 --> 21:38.650
The third one.

21:38.920 --> 21:39.780
The fourth one.

21:40.680 --> 21:41.900
Let's use these.

21:42.510 --> 21:43.870
I'm going to make some coffee.

21:43.870 --> 21:45.470
Wait, let me send them to you.

21:45.920 --> 21:47.110
Turn on your AirDrop

21:47.110 --> 21:47.970
and Bluetooth.

21:50.250 --> 21:51.530
Just email them to me.

21:52.510 --> 21:53.200
Okay.

21:54.820 --> 21:55.350
Sent.

21:58.200 --> 21:59.270
I think she really likes

21:59.270 --> 22:00.730
seeing you look defeated.

22:02.750 --> 22:03.550
I like it too.

22:04.580 --> 22:06.040
I'm going grocery shopping.

22:06.040 --> 22:07.500
I'll make dinner tonight.

22:35.720 --> 22:37.960
Based on what you said on the rooftop
that day,

22:37.960 --> 22:39.240
I improvised a bit.

22:39.240 --> 22:40.700
I've sent it to your email.

22:41.110 --> 22:42.720
If you think it's too artsy,

22:42.720 --> 22:44.180
you can delete some parts.

22:47.110 --> 22:48.110
I'm heading back.

22:48.750 --> 22:50.480
Aren't you staying for dinner?

22:52.510 --> 22:53.550
You guys eat.

23:14.240 --> 23:15.550
Pity is useless.

23:16.920 --> 23:18.680
In a real professional arena,

23:19.750 --> 23:21.480
there's no room for any flaws.

23:22.380 --> 23:24.100
That includes myself.

23:25.830 --> 23:28.260
But when you really stand
in the position you want,

23:28.260 --> 23:29.850
what do decades of hard work

23:30.510 --> 23:32.910
and the blood and sweat
of countless people

23:32.960 --> 23:34.000
even amount to?

23:36.750 --> 23:38.590
Under the banner of the club,

23:39.880 --> 23:40.680
we are merely warriors

23:40.680 --> 23:42.960
united by a primitive totem,

23:44.590 --> 23:46.240
fighting our opponents

23:47.000 --> 23:48.640
in another form.

23:51.310 --> 23:52.880
Once on the field,

23:54.350 --> 23:56.510
we are essentially no different

23:56.510 --> 23:58.790
from the slaves
in the ancient Roman Colosseum

23:58.790 --> 24:00.680
who entertain the nobles.

24:04.700 --> 24:07.900
I didn't even have the courage
to step into that cemetery.

24:09.640 --> 24:11.510
I stood in front of the sink,

24:12.010 --> 24:13.880
looking at myself in the mirror,

24:14.880 --> 24:17.080
with a huge black umbrella covering me.

24:18.550 --> 24:20.160
Suddenly looking back

24:21.240 --> 24:23.160
on the life I had lived,

24:23.680 --> 24:24.920
I saw only misty rain

24:25.720 --> 24:28.580
and could no longer
see the path I had taken clearly.

24:30.170 --> 24:32.300
Maybe football shines brightly.

24:33.350 --> 24:34.200
But it...

24:35.720 --> 24:38.310
never shone on me.

24:53.030 --> 24:54.230
Where is Lin Wanxing?

24:56.350 --> 24:57.400
She went back.

24:58.440 --> 25:01.100
Smiling so affectionately
even after she left?

25:02.640 --> 25:04.110
I knew it.

25:04.110 --> 25:07.960
You just don't know how to please a girl.

25:08.920 --> 25:09.780
How about this?

25:10.790 --> 25:11.880
Let me teach you a trick or two.

25:11.880 --> 25:12.740
What do you say?

25:15.720 --> 25:16.720
Do you need me to remind you

25:16.720 --> 25:18.590
that you've only pursued one girl
in your life,

25:18.590 --> 25:19.400
and that was my sister?

25:19.400 --> 25:20.400
Plus, you failed.

25:21.440 --> 25:22.920
That's because I have high standards.

25:22.920 --> 25:23.720
And let me tell you,

25:23.720 --> 25:25.120
I'm making progress now.

25:25.160 --> 25:26.750
The average time she takes
to reply to my messages

25:26.750 --> 25:28.270
went from 10 hours

25:28.270 --> 25:29.960
down to 2 hours.

25:29.960 --> 25:30.720
How's that?

25:31.400 --> 25:34.400
Her latest reply
was probably telling you to get lost.

25:34.830 --> 25:37.240
Well, if she tells me to get lost, I'll...

25:37.240 --> 25:39.200
definitely fold myself in three

25:39.200 --> 25:40.000
and get lost.

25:40.350 --> 25:41.790
Then can you get lost
and go cook right now?

25:41.790 --> 25:42.720
I'm starving.

25:45.200 --> 25:46.680
Hurry up.

26:02.390 --> 26:03.530
[Winfred Wang, Football Coach]

26:05.790 --> 26:06.680
Winfred?

26:08.820 --> 26:10.570
When I was in the UK,

26:10.890 --> 26:12.550
I heard of someone named Winfred.

26:12.550 --> 26:13.680
He was quite famous.

26:13.820 --> 26:15.820
I remember his nickname was Mr. Win.

26:16.720 --> 26:17.790
That should be me.

26:19.310 --> 26:20.310
A year ago,

26:20.310 --> 26:22.370
I coached at the Nanton Club in the UK.

26:24.270 --> 26:25.730
I've heard a lot about you.

26:26.200 --> 26:27.330
Not only that,

26:27.510 --> 26:28.920
he has a lot of fans

26:28.920 --> 26:30.320
on his personal website.

26:31.310 --> 26:32.750
That's all in the past.

26:35.550 --> 26:36.720
Anyway,

26:36.720 --> 26:38.070
thanks for trusting me.

26:38.400 --> 26:39.480
Let's get started.

26:39.960 --> 26:40.480
Let's go upstairs.

26:40.480 --> 26:41.000
Okay.

26:42.030 --> 26:42.960
I'll go with you.

26:43.120 --> 26:46.910
[Psychology Counseling Room]

26:52.590 --> 26:54.000
Mr. Wang, please.

26:55.000 --> 26:55.950
Junior,

26:56.110 --> 26:57.270
just wait here on the sofa

26:57.270 --> 26:58.160
for a moment.

27:02.410 --> 27:06.020
[Psychology Counseling Room]

27:11.680 --> 27:12.740
Please take a seat.

27:16.640 --> 27:17.470
Mr. Wang,

27:17.840 --> 27:18.880
let's begin.

27:19.780 --> 27:20.580
Relax.

27:20.610 --> 27:21.330
Okay.

27:24.790 --> 27:26.110
So where do we start?

27:27.110 --> 27:28.480
Let's talk about

27:29.110 --> 27:30.710
your psychological trauma.

27:30.960 --> 27:32.890
Are you willing to tell me about it?

27:39.950 --> 27:42.030
One of the players I was most proud of

27:44.050 --> 27:46.580
committed suicide
by jumping off a building.

27:56.070 --> 27:57.310
My next question might be

27:57.310 --> 27:58.680
a bit direct.

27:59.770 --> 28:02.890
Why did your player's suicide

28:02.920 --> 28:05.000
become traumatic for you?

28:05.510 --> 28:06.880
Is it because you were very close,

28:06.880 --> 28:09.350
or because his death was related to you?

28:24.160 --> 28:25.660
It seems you

28:25.800 --> 28:27.780
still don't trust me completely.

28:27.940 --> 28:28.750
It's fine.

28:30.810 --> 28:32.140
Let's not talk about it.

28:32.560 --> 28:33.960
Let's change the subject

28:34.650 --> 28:35.750
and talk about something else.

28:35.750 --> 28:36.900
Talk about what,

28:37.030 --> 28:37.750
Mr. Xiang?

28:41.310 --> 28:42.500
Let's talk...

28:44.370 --> 28:46.030
Let's talk about Lin Wanxing.

28:50.520 --> 28:51.800
How did you meet?

29:01.130 --> 29:01.890
Destiny.

29:03.680 --> 29:04.880
I care about her a lot,

29:05.750 --> 29:07.610
and I want her to be my girlfriend.

29:12.120 --> 29:13.640
Do you really know her?

29:14.370 --> 29:16.300
How much do you know about her past?

29:18.640 --> 29:19.840
That doesn't matter.

29:20.160 --> 29:21.050
Really?

29:21.470 --> 29:23.070
Do you know about her family?

29:23.340 --> 29:25.200
Do you know where her parents are?

29:25.370 --> 29:28.290
An outstanding student like her
actually dropped out of her Ph.D. program.

29:28.290 --> 29:30.310
There are so many contradictions
about her.

29:30.310 --> 29:32.090
Aren't you curious?

29:34.790 --> 29:36.790
Why should I be curious?

29:39.700 --> 29:40.540
Mr. Wang Fa,

29:42.270 --> 29:44.270
from a psychological perspective,

29:44.550 --> 29:47.180
asking a rhetorical question
can indicate hostility.

29:47.180 --> 29:48.100
Relax.

29:48.120 --> 29:49.650
I don't mean anything else.

29:49.740 --> 29:52.440
I just want to help you
understand her better.

29:56.440 --> 29:57.720
So,

29:57.740 --> 29:59.460
do you really

29:59.820 --> 30:01.220
not want to know her past?

30:03.920 --> 30:06.110
She tries so hard to hide herself.

30:06.920 --> 30:09.130
Could there be some unknown dark side?

30:19.200 --> 30:20.610
A person's present

30:21.320 --> 30:23.520
is much more important than their past.

30:27.320 --> 30:28.780
I know her better than you,

30:29.240 --> 30:31.200
and anyone else.

30:31.590 --> 30:33.390
I don't want to dig into her past.

30:34.300 --> 30:36.340
Nor do I want to pry into her secrets.

30:36.370 --> 30:39.000
It doesn't matter
what she has been through,

30:39.620 --> 30:41.350
because I trust her character.

30:41.400 --> 30:42.660
But she isn't sincere.

30:42.990 --> 30:44.150
Don't you mind?

30:44.170 --> 30:46.830
That's because
I'm not worthy of her sincerity.

30:47.560 --> 30:48.760
It's my fault.

30:49.120 --> 30:50.780
She didn't do anything wrong.

30:51.570 --> 30:53.090
End of discussion.

30:54.100 --> 30:57.100
I don't like people
talking about her behind her back.

30:57.980 --> 30:58.750
Okay.

30:59.800 --> 31:01.130
Why aren't you worthy of her sincerity?

31:01.130 --> 31:02.750
What exactly did you do wrong?

31:02.750 --> 31:04.510
Is it because your player died?

31:05.440 --> 31:06.880
Was it a coincidence

31:07.480 --> 31:08.480
that you came to Hongjing,

31:08.480 --> 31:10.480
or did you arrange it deliberately?

31:15.880 --> 31:16.970
Excuse me.

31:17.700 --> 31:19.820
The school suddenly needs Coach Wang
for an emergency.

31:19.820 --> 31:21.420
We'll come back another day.

32:00.880 --> 32:02.860
If you can't
regain your emotional balance,

32:02.860 --> 32:04.460
you can try meditation,

32:04.480 --> 32:05.580
exercise,

32:05.610 --> 32:07.110
or other familiar and safe ways

32:07.110 --> 32:09.040
to relieve stress when you go back.

32:11.750 --> 32:13.010
Ms. Lin,

32:13.920 --> 32:15.360
are you worried about me?

32:19.020 --> 32:21.680
I just don't want the investigation
to go wrong.

32:24.160 --> 32:25.080
Don't worry.

32:25.420 --> 32:26.220
I'm fine.

32:32.200 --> 32:33.330
Did Xiang Zi

32:34.160 --> 32:36.160
ask you any strange questions?

32:37.070 --> 32:37.960
For example?

32:39.070 --> 32:41.200
What do you mean by strange questions?

32:42.280 --> 32:43.050
Nothing.

32:54.000 --> 32:57.940
[Winfred Wang]

33:32.130 --> 33:32.470
[I often feel
that human life is like a butterfly—]

33:32.500 --> 33:32.770
[fragile yet beautiful.
With just a little temptation,]

33:32.800 --> 33:33.030
[one can be led astray,
like a moth flying into the flame.]

33:33.050 --> 33:33.570
[Your opinion is interesting.
I agree with you.]

33:34.000 --> 33:36.250
He finally took the bait.

33:43.990 --> 33:45.120
Who is it?

33:51.270 --> 33:53.200
Xiang Zi visited our website
early this morning.

33:53.200 --> 33:55.260
He contacted Yu Bo for a private chat.

33:55.550 --> 33:56.480
Any gains?

33:57.070 --> 33:59.600
He showed his record
of buying illegal drugs,

34:00.130 --> 34:02.400
confirming he was the one
trading with Kevin.

34:02.400 --> 34:03.670
The evidence is solid.

34:07.000 --> 34:07.850
[Jason's urine test report
will be released soon.]

34:07.870 --> 34:08.830
[He will have to quit.
Prepare the final payment.]

34:11.000 --> 34:11.820
[The weather will be nice tomorrow.
Then let's meet before 3 p.m. tomorrow.]

34:11.840 --> 34:12.530
[King's Cross Station, Locker No. 19.]

34:12.550 --> 34:13.330
[Put the deposit in. I'll go get it.]

34:22.100 --> 34:23.800
[What kind of deal?]

34:24.030 --> 34:26.389
[Purchase Record: Prohibited Drugs]

34:27.000 --> 34:27.420
[This is our last candy delivery.
See you at the same place.]

34:27.440 --> 34:27.949
[Remember, we'll have nothing to do
with each other after this.]

34:34.800 --> 34:36.350
You want to convict me

34:36.679 --> 34:38.120
based on this?

34:38.139 --> 34:40.340
Kevin is already under investigation.

34:40.760 --> 34:42.489
You conspired to drug Jason,

34:42.710 --> 34:45.440
also known as Yang Mingsen,
with banned substances,

34:45.440 --> 34:47.460
causing his suspension,
which led him to commit suicide.

34:47.460 --> 34:48.860
You can't get out of this.

34:50.030 --> 34:51.320
Did you forget

34:51.340 --> 34:53.800
that it was you who replaced
his gummy bears?

34:56.370 --> 34:57.400
He's dead?

34:58.710 --> 35:00.800
Your player was too fragile.

35:01.400 --> 35:02.550
Could it be that you, as his coach,

35:02.550 --> 35:03.360
put too much pressure on him

35:03.360 --> 35:04.760
and drove him to suicide?

35:05.230 --> 35:06.910
He was not my player.

35:06.940 --> 35:08.600
What does it have to do with me?

35:10.420 --> 35:11.710
He's provoking you.

35:11.950 --> 35:12.950
Don't fall for it.

35:20.850 --> 35:21.690
Junior.

35:22.650 --> 35:24.170
I was so good to you before,

35:24.190 --> 35:25.940
but you didn't care about me.

35:26.090 --> 35:28.120
Why are you so attentive
to someone else now?

35:28.120 --> 35:30.500
It's my freedom
to be attentive to whoever I want.

35:30.500 --> 35:31.860
Jason did nothing wrong.

35:31.860 --> 35:33.090
He was innocent.

35:33.660 --> 35:35.260
Why on earth did you harm him?

35:38.550 --> 35:39.000
Yes.

35:40.290 --> 35:41.560
He was innocent.

35:42.840 --> 35:45.360
Because you are the one who was wrong.

35:46.610 --> 35:50.100
[2 Years Ago,
London Psychology Research Institute]

35:48.000 --> 35:48.840
See you tomorrow.

35:48.840 --> 35:50.230
-Bye-bye.
-Bye-bye.

36:07.710 --> 36:09.480
Junior, want some coffee?

36:10.030 --> 36:11.840
No thanks, honey water is fine.

36:29.120 --> 36:30.720
What are you chatting about?

36:33.030 --> 36:34.070
Sorry.

36:34.070 --> 36:35.290
It's fine. No worries.

36:35.290 --> 36:36.930
You look so focused.

36:37.190 --> 36:38.160
Who were you talking to?

36:38.160 --> 36:39.440
A friend of mine.

36:40.860 --> 36:41.930
It's so late.

36:42.440 --> 36:44.270
I need to hurry back and deal with this.

36:44.270 --> 36:45.400
Aren't you leaving?

36:46.770 --> 36:50.560
I need to sort out the rest of my paper.

36:51.030 --> 36:52.430
I'm staying a bit longer.

36:52.550 --> 36:53.420
I'll get going then.

36:53.420 --> 36:54.230
Okay.

36:57.350 --> 36:58.370
Bye, Senior.

36:58.480 --> 36:59.280
Bye-bye.

37:24.220 --> 37:26.200
[I forgot my password.]

37:27.690 --> 37:28.240
[Spade Q]

37:29.980 --> 37:31.840
[Log in]

37:32.410 --> 37:33.020
[Ming]

37:38.550 --> 37:40.340
[Ming]

37:41.900 --> 37:43.840
[Yongchuan University
Psychology Department Student Union]

37:43.860 --> 37:44.700
[Inbox]

37:44.730 --> 37:45.670
[Spade Q,
are you interested in making a deal?]

37:45.700 --> 37:46.900
[I'll pay you well.]

37:50.980 --> 37:59.220
[Recipient]

37:59.240 --> 38:02.670
[I'm Spade Q.]

38:02.700 --> 38:06.830
[What kind of deal?]

38:08.010 --> 38:09.220
You actually

38:09.250 --> 38:10.910
have been snooping on my computer?

38:10.910 --> 38:13.190
Why did he get to chat with you
every day?

38:13.220 --> 38:15.530
Why did you care about him more than me?

38:15.550 --> 38:16.980
I'm your senior.

38:17.090 --> 38:18.480
I like you so much.

38:18.510 --> 38:19.980
Have you ever considered my feelings?

38:19.980 --> 38:21.500
Just for this reason,

38:21.550 --> 38:23.280
you had to kill a person?

38:23.280 --> 38:25.960
In the end, it was because of you,
Lin Wanxing.

38:25.960 --> 38:27.110
I thought if I had money,

38:27.110 --> 38:28.400
you would look at me properly.

38:28.400 --> 38:29.920
But you still ignored me.

38:29.920 --> 38:31.360
You even rejected me.

38:32.960 --> 38:33.820
Let me tell you,

38:35.600 --> 38:37.890
it feels so good to torture you.

38:37.910 --> 38:40.180
Why should you get all the resources?

38:40.230 --> 38:41.360
Why do you always act

38:41.360 --> 38:42.650
so high and mighty?

38:42.800 --> 38:44.760
People like you should suffer a bit.

38:44.760 --> 38:45.840
You should know that

38:45.840 --> 38:48.500
playing with others' feelings
comes at a price!

38:51.800 --> 38:53.360
You are insane.

38:57.320 --> 38:59.110
I hate it when you look at me like that!

38:59.110 --> 39:00.020
Lin Wanxing!

39:05.960 --> 39:06.550
Your hand...

39:06.550 --> 39:07.680
Call the police now!

39:08.590 --> 39:09.550
Watch out!

39:16.440 --> 39:18.320
Let me go! I'll kill you!

39:18.320 --> 39:20.190
Let me go! Let me go!

39:22.220 --> 39:23.220
Let me go!

39:23.240 --> 39:25.800
[Police]

39:48.740 --> 39:50.140
Let's go to the hospital.

39:57.150 --> 39:58.000
Okay.

39:59.150 --> 40:00.100
I got it.

40:01.280 --> 40:02.000
Thank you.

40:07.590 --> 40:09.450
How is it? What did the doctor say?

40:09.730 --> 40:10.930
No bones were broken.

40:11.000 --> 40:12.280
It's just a cut.

40:12.280 --> 40:13.480
It will heal in a week.

40:14.320 --> 40:15.110
That's good.

40:16.360 --> 40:17.550
The police said

40:17.550 --> 40:19.400
when Xiang Zi was being interrogated,

40:19.400 --> 40:21.070
his mental state was very unstable.

40:21.070 --> 40:23.400
They suspect he may have a mental illness.

40:23.410 --> 40:25.150
How will the police handle it next?

40:25.150 --> 40:26.590
The case will be handed over first,

40:26.590 --> 40:29.150
and Xiang Zi will be sent
for a psychiatric evaluation.

40:29.150 --> 40:32.150
They will take the next step
after the results are out.

40:37.400 --> 40:38.530
Thank you for today.

40:39.480 --> 40:40.760
I didn't expect

40:40.760 --> 40:42.020
things to come to this.

40:43.670 --> 40:45.030
f it's okay,

40:45.480 --> 40:47.440
can I go see Ming's mother?

40:47.920 --> 40:48.970
No matter what,

40:49.280 --> 40:51.140
I still want to tell her the truth.

40:53.510 --> 40:54.110
Let's go.

41:02.400 --> 41:05.200
If I had noticed earlier that someone
was using me,

41:06.150 --> 41:07.700
maybe Jason...

41:10.260 --> 41:11.330
I'm sorry.

41:13.670 --> 41:15.110
After it happened,

41:17.920 --> 41:19.480
I avoided it for a long time,

41:22.070 --> 41:23.840
using the excuse
that I had to find the truth

41:23.840 --> 41:25.170
before I could face you.

41:30.390 --> 41:31.790
Jason did nothing wrong.

41:33.820 --> 41:35.280
I was the one who was wrong.

41:37.000 --> 41:40.130
I didn't give him the trust
and support he needed in time.

41:42.110 --> 41:43.570
I didn't protect him well.

41:47.550 --> 41:49.110
The child is gone.

41:51.550 --> 41:53.400
What's the point of

41:53.840 --> 41:55.110
saying all this now?

41:57.070 --> 41:58.480
For so long,

41:59.190 --> 42:01.790
I've also been living in
self-blame and guilt.

42:05.510 --> 42:07.320
I cared about him too little.

42:08.920 --> 42:10.480
Every time he called,

42:11.400 --> 42:12.630
I would either ask him

42:13.160 --> 42:14.820
how many goals he scored today

42:15.380 --> 42:16.860
or ask him

42:16.960 --> 42:18.590
how much his ranking went up.

42:19.920 --> 42:21.880
If only I had cared a little more.

42:23.680 --> 42:25.360
If only I had just asked him,

42:26.320 --> 42:27.280
"Son,

42:27.820 --> 42:29.680
have you been eating well lately?

42:30.360 --> 42:32.760
Are there any new dishes
in the cafeteria?"

42:33.330 --> 42:34.290
"Son,

42:35.440 --> 42:36.840
if you miss me,

42:36.840 --> 42:38.110
just tell me.

42:38.110 --> 42:40.480
I'll fly to the UK to see you."

42:42.650 --> 42:43.560
"Right, son,

42:44.380 --> 42:46.820
that game console you mentioned last time,

42:46.970 --> 42:49.070
the one you wanted,

42:49.710 --> 42:52.580
Mom already bought it for you."

42:57.360 --> 42:58.630
But now,

43:02.510 --> 43:04.360
I have no one to say it to.

43:27.590 --> 43:30.510
Jason didn't do anything wrong.

43:32.110 --> 43:34.630
He was always a good kid.

43:35.830 --> 43:37.400
Ma'am.

43:37.790 --> 43:39.080
Jason...

43:40.400 --> 43:41.510
would definitely not want to see you

43:41.510 --> 43:43.230
live in guilt forever.

43:44.490 --> 43:46.120
The living

43:49.630 --> 43:50.920
must move forward.

44:28.050 --> 44:29.450
Don't let what happened to Jason

44:29.450 --> 44:31.330
happen to another child.

44:32.590 --> 44:34.390
Take good care of your students.

45:05.360 --> 45:06.290
Let's head back.

45:07.170 --> 45:08.030
I'll call a car.

45:09.470 --> 45:10.930
I want to take a walk alone.

45:39.080 --> 45:40.550
♪ There's nothing to fear ♪

45:41.240 --> 45:42.640
♪ Because you're with me ♪
